The '''bleeding edge''' or '''cutting edge''' is a term used to mean something very current, where there may actually be a hazard or risk in using it. the terms relates to a [[sword]].

In the computer world something that was bleeding edge could be a [[GNU/Linux]] distribution. The risks there would include unstable [[software]] or possible damage to [[hardware]] (back in 1999, not true anymore anno 2005)